+# B2 Style Gallery — VISUAL handoff (for a design-focused session)
+
+**Status:** the *plumbing* is built, tested, and on disk (see "What already works"). The
+operator looked at the rendered output and said **"I can't ship this."** Your job is the
+**visual quality** — make the templates and the gallery look like a premium SWFL Data Gulf
+product, NOT a generic stock template. Do **not** rebuild the architecture.
+
+This brief is self-contained. You do not need the prior chat.
+
+---
+
+## Your mission (one sentence)
+
+Make the brand-style gallery and its templates **look shippable** — on-brand SWFL data,
+premium typography/spacing/charts, and readable thumbnails — **without breaking the
+token system, the tests, or email/print compatibility.**
+
+---
+
+## What already works — BUILD ON THIS, do not redo it
+
+The data flow, brand injection, routes, and gallery logic are done and green. Touch these
+for **visual** reasons only; their behavior is correct.
+
+- **Render engine (brand-agnostic):** `renderHtmlTemplate(slug, tokens)`
+  (`lib/templates/render-html-template.ts`) — `{{TOKEN}}` find-and-replace. One shell serves
+  every brand; only token VALUES differ. Don't change this contract.
+- **Gallery (in-app, `/project/[id]`):** `app/project/[id]/StyleGallery.tsx` — 3 tabs
+  (Email / PDF / Website), live `srcdoc` iframe thumbnails, click-to-zoom lightbox, per-lane
+  actions (Email → "Send to me", PDF → "Open as PDF", Website → "Build this style"), and the
+  "Create In Your Brand Colors and Logo!" teaser card.
+- **Brand inputs:** `app/project/[id]/ProjectDetail.tsx` Branding section — primary/accent
+  color pickers + logo URL; Save → `router.refresh()` re-skins thumbnails.
+- **Server render of previews:** `app/project/[id]/render-previews.ts` +
+  `app/project/[id]/style-catalog.ts` (lane → slug/templateId map).
+- **Routes:** `app/api/email/test-send/route.ts` (transactional send-to-self),
+  `app/api/projects/[id]/print/route.ts` (branded doc → `window.print()`).
+- **Shared brand/token constants:** `lib/email/templates/preview-brand.ts`,
+  `lib/email/templates/build-test-send.ts`.
+- **Tests (KEEP GREEN):** `bun test lib/email/templates "app/project/[id]"` — 12 pass.
+
+**See it / iterate:** `bun scripts/preview-style-gallery.mts` writes
+`style-gallery-preview.html` (open in a browser — no app/env needed). This is your visual
+feedback loop. Regenerate after every change and judge: *does this look shippable?*
+
+---
+
+## Why it doesn't look shippable (diagnosis with evidence)
+
+1. **Generic finance-demo data — the #1 problem.** The email + doc shells ship stock content,
+   not SWFL. It reads as a template someone bought, not our product:
+   - `email-hero.html:32` — "Total Portfolio Value", "$4.2M", "847 Active ZIPs"
+   - `email-hbar.html` — "Revenue by Region": **Northeast / Southeast / Midwest / Mountain / Pacific**
+   - `email-table.html:30` — "Market Segment Overview"; cols "Segment / Revenue / Units"
+   - `email-compare.html:56` — "Total Revenue"
+   - `doc-hbar.html:137` — "Revenue by Metropolitan Region"; rows "Northeast Metro · **ZIP clusters 100xx–129xx**", "Pacific Coast · 900xx–961xx" (**non-Florida ZIPs**)
+   - `doc-donut.html:151` — "Portfolio Composition by Asset Type", "Q2 2025"
+   - `doc-sparkline.html:127` — "Monthly Revenue Trend"
+   - `doc-split.html:196` — "Northeast · Q2 2025 · ZIP clusters 100xx–129xx"
+   - `doc-hero.html:188` — "Q2 2025 · Portfolio Performance"
+2. **Unreadable thumbnails.** The gallery scales a full 600px email / 1040px letter-size doc
+   down to a ~248px card via CSS transform → text is microscopic. The thumbnail needs to read
+   at a glance (cover/crop the hero region, or render larger, or a tasteful framed preview).
+3. **Logo treatment.** SWFL default logo (`logo-transparent.svg`, a 512×512 square wave mark)
+   renders as a tiny square at `height:28`. Needs a better lockup; the teaser uses a "YOUR LOGO"
+   data-URI wordmark that's placeholder-crude.
+4. **Generic chrome.** Spacing, type scale, chart styling are "fine" but not premium — they
+   don't match the polish of the in-house `viz/` templates or the brand design kit (below).
+
+---
+
+## The strongest asset you have: the `viz/` templates + the brand kit
+
+- **`templates/html/viz/*.html`** (flood-exposure, corridor-positioning, seasonal-exposure,
+  storm-year-timeline, freight-nowcast) are **already SWFL-branded and well-designed** — they
+  are the **quality bar** and a source of real SWFL framing/data. **Strongly consider featuring
+  the viz cards in the gallery** (add to `style-catalog.ts`) or porting their look into the
+  email/doc shells. They token-replace through the same engine (lowercase data tokens + brand).
+- **`docs/fiverr-briefs/assets/`** — the brand design system: `Colors_Accent.html`,
+  `Colors_Direction.html`, `Colors_Surfaces.html`, `Type_MetricStack.html`, `Type_Verdict.html`,
+  `Chat-Charts-Standalone.html`. **Match this type scale, color usage, and metric-card style.**
+- **`app/globals.css`** — platform palette (`--gulf-midnight #0a1419`, `--gulf-teal #0a8078`,
+  `--mangrove #5bc97a` bullish, `--sunset-coral #e08158` bearish, `--neutral-gold #d4b370`) and
+  the `@media print` block. The app shell is **dark**; the email/doc shells are **light**. Both
+  are legit — keep each surface authentic to where it renders.
+- **`templates/html/README.md`** — the full 17-token contract. Read before editing shells.
+
+---
+
+## SWFL sample-data kit (use instead of the finance demo data)
+
+Replace the generic content with believable SWFL examples. These are **style samples**, so
+illustrative numbers are acceptable — but keep them **SWFL-specific and plausible**; prefer
+real cited values lifted from the `viz/` templates or a live master read
+(`mcp__swfl__swfl_fetch` / `https://www.swfldatagulf.com/api/b/master?view=speak`) so it reads
+authentic. Do **not** invent precision below ZIP grain (house-level numbers).
+
+- **Places / ZIPs:** Fort Myers 33901 · Cape Coral 33904 / 33914 · Fort Myers Beach 33931
+  ($30,074/yr avg annual flood loss, +60 bps — real, from CLAUDE.md) · Gateway 33913 ·
+  Lehigh Acres 33936 · Bonita Springs 34134 · Naples 34102 / 34103 / 34108.
+- **Corridors:** US-41 (Tamiami Trail), Colonial Blvd, Pine Island Rd, Daniels Pkwy,
+  Airport-Pulling Rd, Immokalee Rd, Cleveland Ave, Bonita Beach Rd.
+- **Metrics that fit each template:** median sale price / ZHVI · median rent (ZORI) ·
+  avg annual flood loss (AAL) · permit counts · vacancy % · traffic (AADT) · tourist-development-tax.
+- **County framing:** Lee & Collier (6-county scope: Charlotte, Collier, Glades, Hendry, Lee,
+  Sarasota). Never label a county figure as a ZIP figure.
+
+Example re-skins: `email-hero` → "Median Sale Price — Lee County" / "$415,000" / "Cape Coral
+33914 · Fort Myers 33901 · Bonita 34134". `doc-hbar` "Revenue by Region" → "Median Rent by
+Corridor" with US-41 / Colonial / Pine Island rows. `doc-donut` → "Flood-Zone Exposure by ZIP".
+
+---
+
+## HARD GUARDRAILS (breaking any of these breaks the system)
+
+1. **Keep the `{{TOKEN}}` system. NEVER hardcode brand colors/fonts/logo.** Colors, fonts,
+   `BORDER_RADIUS`, `COMPANY_NAME`, `LOGO_URL`, `TAGLINE`, `WEBSITE_URL` stay tokens — the whole
+   point is brand-agnostic re-skin. Sample DATA (numbers, place names, labels) may be hardcoded
+   in the shell. If you add a token, add it to `lib/email/templates/preview-brand.ts`
+   (`EXTRA_PREVIEW_TOKENS`) and `templates/html/README.md`.
+2. **Email = inbox-safe.** `templates/html/email/*` and the `shell-*` files: inline CSS only,
+   table layout, ≤600px, mobile-fluid, **no `<style>` blocks, no JavaScript, no external fonts**
+   (Gmail/Outlook strip them). Don't "modernize" with flexbox/grid in email.
+3. **Shells keep CAN-SPAM tokens.** `shell-*.html` must retain `{{{RESEND_UNSUBSCRIBE_URL}}}`
+   and `{{PHYSICAL_ADDRESS}}` (the broadcast route hard-blocks without the unsubscribe token).
+4. **Doc templates keep `@media print`.** PDF is `window.print()`, letter-size. Don't remove
+   print rules; verify a doc still prints cleanly.
+5. **Keep tests green.** Run `bun test lib/email/templates "app/project/[id]"` after changes.
+   The render tests assert the brand primary reaches output + no unfilled `{{TOKEN}}`; the
+   send-builder test asserts SWFL defaults (`#0F2035`) and the default logo. Re-data won't break
+   these; renaming/removing tokens will.
+6. **Builds are free; SEND is the only paywall** (operator policy). Do not add any payment gate.
+7. **Don't touch the plumbing logic** — render pipeline, routes, gallery data flow, brand
+   resolution. You may restyle `StyleGallery.tsx` (thumbnail framing, card/lightbox CSS) and the
+   `ProjectDetail` Branding layout, but not their behavior.
+
+---
+
+## Acceptance criteria
+
+- **Visual (judge on `style-gallery-preview.html` + the in-app gallery):** templates read as a
+  premium SWFL product — on-brand SWFL data (no "Portfolio/Region/Segment", no non-FL ZIPs),
+  clean type scale matching the brand kit, polished charts, a real logo lockup. Thumbnails are
+  legible at card size; the lightbox is crisp.
+- **Brand re-skin still works:** changing primary/accent/logo re-colors every template (prove
+  with the red/gold sample brand in the preview script).
+- **Teaser** clearly says "Create In Your Brand Colors and Logo!" and looks intentional.
+- **Automated:** `bun test lib/email/templates "app/project/[id]"` green · `npx eslint <touched>`
+  clean · `npx next build` compiles + passes TypeScript (note: static prerender of `/charts`
+  fails locally for lack of Supabase env — pre-existing, unrelated; ignore it).
+- **Compatibility:** at least one email opened in Gmail renders correctly; at least one doc
+  prints cleanly to PDF.
+
+---
+
+## Out of scope / don't do
+
+- No architecture changes, no new mandatory gates, no live-data binding of the static shells
+  (the React website deliverables already do live data; these are style samples).
+- No broadcast / daily-email / others'-email work. No public showcase page.
+- No renaming the token contract or the lane structure unless you also update
+  `style-catalog.ts`, `preview-brand.ts`, `README.md`, and the tests in the same change.
+
+---
+
+## Files you'll most likely touch
+
+- `templates/html/email/email-{hero,table,compare,ranked,hbar,report}.html` (re-data + polish)
+- `templates/html/doc/doc-{hero,hbar,donut,sparkline,split}.html` (re-data + polish)
+- `app/project/[id]/StyleGallery.tsx` (thumbnail framing, card + lightbox styling)
+- `app/project/[id]/ProjectDetail.tsx` (Branding section layout only)
+- maybe `app/project/[id]/style-catalog.ts` (feature the `viz/` cards), `preview-brand.ts`
+  (better default logo / company tokens), `templates/html/README.md` (update data descriptions)
+
+Ship in the same change: green tests, a regenerated `style-gallery-preview.html` to eyeball,
+and a `SESSION_LOG.md` entry. Push only on the operator's go (standing no-autonomous-push rule).
